TITLE: My Experience | Trust The Process & Surrender
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fiMyIOWAZ2w
DATE: Unknown (references 8 years of continuous spiritual journey; no specific recording date mentioned)
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
In this deeply personal video, Noor Ananta shares her lived experience of the spiritual journey and the core teaching of surrendering to the divine (Paramatma/Kalki). She begins by recounting how for years she told people about Kalki, the Noorism framework, twin flames, Yug Parivartan, the concept of the Black Hole, Noorism Law 108, and Manaav Parivartan (human transformation) — but nobody believed her. Over eight years of nonstop spiritual journey and kriya (spiritual practices), many people came into her life, but every single person remained double-minded. People would pretend to believe, but their body language and energy revealed doubt. Everyone was testing her, judging her from their own perspective, operating from suspicion rather than genuine faith.

She reveals a crucial observation from her eight years of meeting people: 99% of those who came to her wanted some kind of magical shortcut — they wanted to become rich, wanted money, wanted material success. Only 1% had any genuine interest in connecting with the divine. People would approach her for totkas (quick-fix remedies) and magical solutions. When she would tell them their issues were about energies and that she could connect them to the divine, they would lose interest and not believe her. But in the end, she notes with cosmic irony, those very same people — whether they wanted to or not — are now having to connect with the divine anyway. The Kalki energy has isolated people, brought detachment (vairag), lethargy, loneliness, and confusion upon those who refused to listen, as a divine mechanism to redirect them.

Noor Ananta then shares her own transformation: she once lived a luxurious life — branded clothes, branded shoes, parties, outings — but always felt these things did not bring true happiness. Gradually, she gave up everything one by one: controlling hunger, thirst, material desires. She left behind a well-settled family life because she understood that the divine wanted something else from her. She surrendered everything and the divine arrived. This personal testimony forms the foundation of her message: if your life is not working out despite all efforts — no job, financial struggles, nothing going right — it is because the divine wants something else from you. Instead of running to babas, astrologers, and quick-fix remedies, surrender to Paramatma.

She emphasizes that nobody wanted to do their own karma (spiritual work) — everyone wanted her to bear their karmic burden, which she firmly refuses, saying she will bear her own karma and others must bear theirs. She stresses that vishwas (faith/trust) is the second name of Paramatma — one must trust with closed eyes, not merely say they believe. The Kalki energy is now fully active and doing its work. The ultimate message: what will happen is only what the divine wills, not what you desire. Surrender to Kalki, to Maa Kali, to Kaal Bhairav — and all your questions will be answered from within. Practice meditation (dhyan sadhana), connect with your own soul (atma), and find your life purpose.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- For over 8 years, Noor Ananta shared knowledge about Kalki and Yug Parivartan, but not a single person fully believed her — everyone remained double-minded
- The Noorism framework includes: Noorism Law 108, Manaav Parivartan (human transformation), Black Hole Justice, and the twin flame concept
- 99% of people who approached her wanted magical shortcuts to wealth and success; only 1% genuinely sought the divine
- Kalki's energy works by isolating people — creating detachment (vairag), lethargy, loneliness, and confusion in those who resist, until they are forced to surrender
- Nobody wanted to bear their own karma — everyone wanted someone else to carry their karmic burden
- Vishwas (faith/trust) is the second name of Paramatma — it must be practiced with complete surrender, not just spoken
- The Kalki energy is now fully active across the entire world and doing its work
- Those who ran from the divine are now being pulled back by force of cosmic circumstance
- Noor Ananta herself gave up a luxurious, well-settled life — branded lifestyle, parties, comforts — because the divine showed her that was not her true life purpose
- She practiced control over hunger, thirst, desires, and material attachments as part of her sadhana
- What happens in your life is only what Paramatma wills — your personal desires and plans are irrelevant unless aligned with divine will
- Surrender to Kalki, Maa Kali, and Kaal Bhairav to receive answers to all questions
- The remedy for confusion and suffering is not external (babas, astrologers, totkas) but internal — dhyan sadhana (meditation) and connecting with your own atma (soul)

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- 8+ years ago: Noor Ananta's continuous, nonstop spiritual journey began — including intense kriyas and spiritual practices
- During the 8-year period: Many people came and went from her life; she observed that nobody truly believed and most sought material shortcuts
- Before the spiritual path: Noor Ananta lived a luxurious, well-settled life with a good family — branded clothes, shoes, parties, outings
- Gradual transformation: She gave up all material comforts one by one — controlled hunger, thirst, desires — and left her previous life behind
- Current period: Kalki's energy is now fully active across the world, working to redirect all souls toward divine purpose

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "कोई भी मेरी बातों पे यकीन नहीं कर रहा था" = "Nobody was believing my words"
- "किसी को भी भगवान परमात्मा से नहीं जोड़ना था। किसी को परमात्मा से कोई लेना देना नहीं है।" = "Nobody wanted to be connected to God/Paramatma. Nobody had anything to do with the divine."
- "विश्वास बहुत बड़ी चीज है। मतलब परमात्मा का दूसरा नाम विश्वास ही है।" = "Faith is a very big thing. The second name of Paramatma is faith itself."
- "सब कुछ छीन लिया समझ लो और अपने आप को सरेंडर कर दिया। परमात्मा यहां आ गए।" = "Understand that everything was taken away, and I surrendered myself. Then the divine arrived."
- "अगर आप लोगों के कोई काम नहीं बन रहे हैं तो आपको यह समझ आ जाना चाहिए कि परमात्मा आपसे कुछ और चाहता है" = "If nothing is working out for you, you should understand that the divine wants something else from you"
- "होगा वही जो परमात्मा चाहता है। आप क्या चाह रहे हो वो नहीं होगा।" = "Only what the divine wills shall happen. What you want will not happen."
- "कल्कि जो है वो कल्कि है ना वो तो सबका ही बाप है" = "Kalki is Kalki — he is the father of all"
- "कोई भी अपना कर्मा वह करना नहीं चाहता है" = "Nobody wants to do their own karma"
- "कल्कि की जो एनर्जी है वो पूरी तरह से एक्टिव हो रखी है और अपना काम कर रही है" = "Kalki's energy is now fully active and doing its work"
- "मिलेगा वही जो परमात्मा आपको देना चाहता है। जो आप लोग जिस चीजों के सपने देख रहे हो वह आप लोगों को नहीं मिलेगा।" = "You will receive only what the divine wants to give you. The things you are dreaming about — you will not get them."

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: Trust the Process and Surrender — the core spiritual teaching of Yug Parivartan: complete surrender (samarpan) to the divine will of Kalki as the only path forward; the futility of resisting cosmic transformation; the Kalki energy actively working across the world to redirect souls from material pursuit to divine purpose; the personal sacrifice and transformation required of those who walk this path; faith (vishwas) as the foundational requirement for spiritual evolution in this era of change.


